--- !u!114 &3000054665768344107
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 5624992500406450016}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: f4688fdb7df04437aeb418b961361dc5, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  m_Material: {fileID: 0}
  m_Color: {r: 1, g: 1, b: 1, a: 1}
  m_RaycastTarget: 1
  m_RaycastPadding: {x: 0, y: 0, z: 0, w: 0}
  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "Welcome to the AR Wetlands Watchers mobile application. Your privacy is
    important to us. \n\nThis Privacy Policy outlines what information we do (and
    do not) collect, how we use device permissions, and your rights regarding privacy
    and security.\n\n1. No User Login or Credentials Collected\nWe do not collect,
    store, or transmit any personally identifiable information (PII) or user credentials.
    Our application is designed to work completely offline and without requiring
    user login or authentication.\n\nWhat this means:\nNo usernames, passwords, emails,
    or personal accounts are ever requested or stored.\n\nThe app functions entirely
    on-device.\n\nThere are no back-end servers collecting data from the user.\n\nStandards
    Followed:\nOWASP Mobile Top 10 (M2: Insecure Authentication)\n\nAndroid and iOS
    security best practices\n\nCompany Privacy Policy v1.2, Section 3.1: \u201CMinimal
    User Data Collection\u201D\n\n2. Camera Access Permission\nOur application uses
    Augmented Reality (AR), which requires access to your device\u2019s camera.\n\nWe
    will:\n\nPrompt you for camera permission only when you tap \u201CStart\u201D
    on the main menu.\n\nProvide a clear explanation if permission is denied and
    allow you to retry or open system settings.\n\nWhat we do not do:\nWe do not
    record or store any video or images from the camera.\n\nCamera data is used only
    in real-time for AR functionality.\n\nStandards Followed:\nAndroid Developer
    Guidelines: Runtime Permissions\n\nApple Human Interface Guidelines: \u201CRequesting
    Access\u201D\n\nNIST SP 800-124r2 and SP 800-53 privacy controls\n\n3. In-App
    Privacy Policy Display\nTo ensure transparency, we include a Privacy Policy button
    in the main menu of the app. Tapping this button will open a readable page with
    this policy, which you can scroll through and dismiss using an \u201CX\u201D
    button or swipe gesture.\n\nRequirements met:\nClearly describes camera use and
    data handling\n\nEasily accessible from both the app and app store listing\n\nComplies
    with GDPR, CCPA, and other regional privacy regulations\n\nStandards Followed:\nIEEE
    P1912 Privacy Standards\n\nGoogle Play & Apple App Store privacy requirements\n\nNIST
    SP 800-53 (PR.PO-1: Transparency)\n\nTermly 2022 UI Recommendations\n\nYour Rights
    and Choices\nYou may decline camera permission, in which case the AR experience
    will not run.\n\nYou may uninstall the app at any time. No data will remain on
    your device.\n\nContact\nFor any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy,
    please contact our team via the support page on the app store listing.\n\n"
